Anise#Anise (Pimpinella anisum L.) is a culinary spice from the Apiaceae family,1 originating in the region(s) of E. Mediterranean; W. Asia.2 It is used for its fruit and oil, primarily for pastries, candies, liquors. Its aroma is described as licorice-like, sweet, with a heat index of 1.3
