Caraway#Caraway (Carum carvi L.) is a culinary spice from the Apiaceae family,1 originating in the region(s) of Mediterranean; Eurasia.2 It is used for its fruit, primarily for breads, sausages, cheese; carminative. Its aroma is described as warm, sweet, anise-like, with a heat index of 1.3
