Cardamom#Cardamom (Elettaria cardamomum (L.) Maton) is a culinary spice from the Zingiberaceae family,1 originating in the region(s) of India.2 It is used for its fruit (seed pods, capsules), primarily for desserts, coffees, curries. Its aroma is described as pungent, eucalyptus-like, with a heat index of 2.3
